title: Grateful Dead Live at Seattle Center Coliseum on 1979-07-01
lineage: Analog Sound Preservation: MAC >> Nakamichi CR7a => Korg MR-1000 >> DSF [1-bit 5.6448 MHz Stereo] >> Korg MR-1000 => Korg AudioGate >> WAV [24/96]
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step-> Franklin's Tower, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Peggy-O, Minglewood Blues, Stagger Lee, El Paso, Brown Eyed Women, Passenger

Set 2

Don't Ease Me In, Samson & Delilah, Sugaree, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Space-> Stella Blue-> Truckin'-> Around & Around, E: Shakedown Street

reviews.review_text: Beautiful Recording This is a wonderful recording of a fine show.  Please do yourselves a favor and at least check out the Half-Step. Garcia's solos are focused and inspired. I love the comment from a guy close to the mics - "this is one helluva sound system!" This recording puts you RIGHT THERE, nestled amongst fellow heads feeding off the band's positive energy.

Great Recording but misslabeled This is a great recording of a great show, however this is missing Mexicali Blues, and there are two copies of Passenger. Everything from Mexicali to Brown Eyed Women is mislabeled. Mexicali should be changed to Peggy-O, and continue the pattern. the tracks labeled as BEW And Passenger are Identical.

This is one of the best shows on the archive! Mexicali Blues is definitely NOT missing on this recording.  The 2 Passenger error is kind of a treat.  This version of passenger will steal your face. If you are a simple listener, 2 times through this version will not bother you, I swear!

Both sets are just splendid!  The recording is so beautiful you will weep, I swear!

The interplay between Jerry and Bob must be heard.  From Half-Step through Shakedown--they are in lock step. You can just really hear the difference between an "on" night and the "off" listening to a show like this. Brent is just bringin' it less than 90 days after taking his seat at the keys.  Fun, fun, fun!!  Sugaree fans---STOP and LISTEN!  A second set super version awaits along w/ a magical Terrapin and poignant and powerful Playin'.  The backwater of set 2 goes from a placid pond  to class 5 whitewater.....
